## Task: Web Workflow UI: Offset failure-path nodes with colored wire paths

When rendering workflow graphs, create offset link nodes for failure paths to avoid collisions and overlapping when multiple pathways exist. Layout example:

    [ node a ] - failed -> +
        |                  |
     succeeded             |
        |                  |
    [ node b ] - failed -> +
        |                  |
     succeeded             |
        |                  |
        V                  V
     [ DONE ]          [ ABORT ]

Use this approach to isolate wire paths from one another as much as possible. Use coloration to distinguish different paths: succeeded=green, failed=red, then blue, yellow, magenta, etc. for other non-success/failure pathways.
